headline.print_headline: Florida Examines Possible First Case of Native Zika
headline.main: Zika Investigated in Florida; Possible First Homegrown Case in U.S.

snippet: If the case is confirmed, it would be the first time the Zika virus had been transmitted locally by mosquitoes in the United States....
abstract: Florida Dept of Health says it is investigating what it believes could be first homegrown case of Zika virus in United States; 'possible non-travel-related' case has been reported in Miami-Dade County.
